Package: timesfm
Title: R Interface to 'TimesFM', a Foundation Model for Time Series
    Forecasting
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Matt", "O'Reilly", email = "fermoymatt@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A thin wrapper around the 'TimesFM' 'Python' package from Google
    Research (<https://github.com/google-research/timesfm>). Provides
    zero-shot probabilistic forecasting of univariate time series from a
    pretrained foundation model, with no training or tuning.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Imports:
    reticulate,
    utils
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.10) with the 'timesfm' package (see
    install_timesfm())
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
